26/01/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On Friday (24 January), Republika Srpska Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic made a public appeal to all war crimes suspects, including Radovan Karadzic, to surrender to the UN war crimes tribunal. 
The appeal followed a meeting with the US envoy for war crimes, Pierre-Richard Prosper. 
Mikerevic said the government will offer guarantees to each suspect for temporary release on bail.He also suggested that war crimes suspects could aid their country's development by turning themselves in. 
(BiH Federation TV - 25/01/03; FoNet, B92 Radio and TV - 24/01/03)
